bio.experienceSummary: Hi I'm Nayreen! I have 4 years of experience with kids. I babysat all ages. I love kids! I'm willing to teach, play with, dress up, bathe, put the little snug bugs to bed, and more! My schedule is flexible and I want to fill up my hours as much as possible for the summer. I've been volunteering at my local first aid squad for 3 years now and went to EMT school and I'm getting my emt certification. I'm currently getting a psychology and health studies degree and I'm also an anatomy major. I'm going to become a certified phlebotomist soon. I can provide basic Life support in any emergency + I'm CPR certified. I offer $20/hr for one child, $24 for 2 children/hr, $27 for 3 children/hr. Please don't hesitate to ask me any questions :)

ONLY LOOKING IN NYC! 
Hi! I'm a recent college graduate, earning a bachelor's degree in Musical Theatre and Political Science. Because of my passion for the arts, I love working with kids on arts and crafts projects, or any way they like to use their imagination! I love pets (I had a lively golden retriever for 12 years) and love to cook. I have been babysitting since I was 13, and have experience with children as young as 6 months and as old as 16. I am only looking for jobs in NYC!

I've always had a passion for helping children grow and develop, which is why I became a childcare provider. I want to have a positive impact on their lives and help support families by providing reliable childcare. I'm patient, creative, and friendly, and I love playing games with children, from outdoor sports to board games and educational games. With more than 20 years of experience caring for children and my Early Childhood Education degree, I'm well-equipped to provide a safe and nurturing environment for your child. I'm certified in First Aid and CPR, and I've taken coursework in Early Child Development. I'm happy to help with cooking, meal preparation, and light housekeeping and my house can be flexible on Monday, Tuesday and Thursday. I hope to have the opportunity to care for your child/children and help them learn and grow!

description.originalText: Grace is a caring, reliable babysitter who truly loves children. She connects with them effortlessly, keeps them engaged with fun activities, and ensures they feel valued. Her warmth and dedication make her a joy to have, and I highly recommend her to any family.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello! My name is Princess, and I am a 24-year-old college student majoring in nursing. With over 8 years of experience caring for children, including those with disabilities, I am passionate about creating a safe, nurturing, and joyful environment for kids of all ages-from infants to teenagers.

I have been surrounded by children for most of my life and am eager to bring my skills and enthusiasm to families in need of reliable childcare. I am well-versed in diaper changing, cooking meals, performing household cleaning, helping with homework, and providing transportation to school or other appropriate destinations.

My goal is to support each child's growth and happiness by offering attentive, loving care, and creating a positive environment that encourages their development and well-being.

description.originalText: We booked Princess to care for our 9 mo baby and she was wonderful. She was punctual and has a warm personality. Our baby was immediately taken to her. Iâ€™d absolutely hire Princess again!

bio.experienceSummary:
My passion for nurturing young minds and supporting families led me to become a childcare provider with over a year of experience. I am patient, creative, and friendly, and I strive to create a safe, nurturing environment for children. I am comfortable enforcing household rules and have excellent communication skills, ensuring parents are always informed about their child's day.

I love playing a variety of games with children, including outdoor sports, board games, and educational games that promote learning. I am also trained in First Aid, CPR, and am a Certified Nursing Assistant, ensuring the well-being of the children in my care.

I am available to provide care for one child, and I am happy to help with cooking, meal preparation, carpooling, and light housekeeping. I am confident that I can provide reliable, high-quality childcare services, and I look forward to the opportunity to support your family.

Hello, my name is Barbara, 21 years old, I have driver license and my own car, I live in Hillside.
I have 4 years and plus experience! 
I always take care of kids at my house when parents need to go out.
I worked 6 months in a family house with a 3 months baby, 3 years old girl and 5 year boy. 
I was working in a day care, but is too far for me and trying to get a new job! I have love and patience in everything I do, trust me. I will love work for your family, I'm available all week, I really need a job and I can start soon as possible, thank you!

Hello! During this time, I am available on weekends or a couple of days a week. Send in the hours you need and I'll be sure to answer as soon as I can.

My name is Victoria and am an accountant by day! I love spending time with kids and having been blessed with a huge family has given me much experience as well! I love to read, make arts and crafts and play sports. For the time being, I am available afternoons and weekends Sat-Sun at anytime. If you ever need someone around these times I am more than willing to lend a hand! Thank you.

description.displayText:
Victoria has been a great caregiver for our family.  She helped out after school with my two boys - 12 and 15 - until we went to virtual learning.  She was always friendly, fun and professional and got along great with everyone.  I really appreciated that she was consistently reliable and timely when arriving and picking my kids up from school and after school activities.  I could depend on her to have delicious meals ready for them, to help my younger one with homework when asked, and to keep in communication with them since the time they needed rides sometimes varied every day depending on variable schedules.  

I found that Victoria always had a great attitude, was flexible and responsive and communicated regularly with me for updates and on how to make our afternoons flow smoothly and to help me have everything in good order so that I could spend quality time with my family when I got home from work.   I definitely recommend her!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi, I'm Laura! I've been around children since I was 7-year-old with the birth of my first niece and haven't stopped since. I'm a proud mama of 3, and have a degree in Early Childhood Education. Since graduation in 2009, I've worked in child care centers teaching little minds. 
I have over 10 years of experience. I can help with Travel and Carpooling.
I have taken a step back from having an entire classroom and love working with a smaller group- having a close and personal relationship with one or two families while their children grow and learn.

description.displayText: Laura was reliable, trustworthy and my kids just loved her! She babysat my kids from the time they were toddlers until they were almost teenagers! She is still someone I talk to to this day!
description.originalText: Laura was reliable, trustworthy and my kids just loved her! She babysat my kids from the time they were toddlers until they were almost teenagers! She is still someone I talk to to this day!

bio.experienceSummary: I've been working with kids for as long as I can remember. I absolutely adore them. Everyone I meet says I am fantastic with children and they see the love I have for them. I just think it's special to grow a bond with kids and be someone that they will never forget, because hopefully I made a positive impact on their lives.  These kids are like best friends to me and vice versa. I also go to school full time and am studying early childhood education to hopefully become an elementary school teacher.

Hello! My name is Sydney, and I'm currently pursuing my nursing degree. I have been passionate about childcare for over five years, caring for children ranging from 6 months to 13 years old. My experience includes creating engaging activities, ensuring safety at all times, and fostering a nurturing environment where children can learn and grow. I love being a positive influence in children's lives and am dedicated to providing attentive care.

description.originalText: Sydney was very welcoming, clear in how to take care of children. I recommend her.
